@NODE MajorBugs

            ===================================================
                                MAJOR BUGS
            ===================================================

            These bugs are  "dangerous"  in the sense that they
            can force, in one way or another,  EasInt to break,
            with the consequent loss of the Panel curretly edi-
            ted.


            "RUN UNTIL" EMBEDDED COMMAND
            ---------------------------------------------------
            This command can cause problems  since it is useful
            only  when the interface code  is invoked  with the
            "Dialog Box" command; instead, EasInt internally u-
            ses the command  "Dialog Open",  which should clash
            with an eventual "RU".The program is halted by AMOS
            with an error message  ( the screen system seems to
            get corrupted, too - NOT my fault!!!)


            DIRECT EDITOR
            ---------------------------------------------------
            When a program is modified through this editor,  it
            is automatically debugged;  though,  in some cases,
            this operations leads to an infinite loop. Save the
            Panel BEFORE editing it by hand!!!

@ENDNODE

@NODE MinorFlaws

            ===================================================
                                MINOR FLAWS
            ===================================================

            These are little (and sometimes irritating)  things
            which could (and would) have been fixed easily.
            They shouldn't provoke any serious damage.


            PALETTE REQUESTER:
            ---------------------------------------------------
            ° When you pick a colour,  the bars are not automa-
              tically positioned according to the RGB values of
              the selected colour
            ° there is not  a box showing  how the colour being
              modified looks like;  just the small box used for
              selection, which is, sadly, half ghosted with the
              previous colour. Stupid, hUh?!


            OUTLINE GRAPHIC MODE
            ---------------------------------------------------
            When drawing a box using a pattern with the outline
            mode ON, the borders are not drawn. AFAIR, this was
            an AMOS problem with the "SP" interface command: in
            fact it does not seem to consider the 2nd parameter
            (outline ON/OFF(0/1, as stated in the user manual))


            ONLINE HELP & MENU SHORTCUTS
            ---------------------------------------------------
            If you pick a menu item with its shortcut  when the
            help is active,  the  first page of explanations is
            directly skipped (in case there are two or more pa-
            ges).  This doesn't happen if the selection is done
            with the right mouse button


            RESOURCES MENU
            ---------------------------------------------------
            The menu item "Design/Resources"  is not accessible
            when editing  a Panel which doesn't make use of re-
            sources. This is not true when a Panel of this kind
            is loaded from disk. Not very important, indeed.


            TITLE OF PANEL
            ---------------------------------------------------
            This gave me a lot of problems. I do not absouletly 
            remember  which  were  its strange effects, but one 
            thing is sure:  when using the "title" option,  you
            could face some problems with the gfx updates.

@ENDNODE

